HEADWORD: Epigynous
<hw>E*pig"y*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>epi-</ets> + Gr. <?/ woman, female: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧pigyne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Adnate to the
surface of the ovary, so as to be apparently inserted upon the top of
it; -- said of stamens, petals, sepals, and also of the disk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epihyal</ent>⟦br⟧
